  "title": "Architectural Coordinator #79901",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Construction</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Architectural Coordinator</strong></li><li>Working Location: Jurong/Island Wide</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon - Fri 8.00am - 6.00pm; Sat 8.00am - 12.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $5,500 + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Review architectural drawings, shop drawings, and BIM models; ensure they are consistent with specs, codes, and client requirements.</li><li>Coordinate interfaces between architectural, structural, and MEP works; manage RFIs and track responses.</li><li>Plan and manage submission of drawings, materials, samples, mock-ups, and method statements; maintain approval logs.</li><li>Assist with authority-related submissions and clearances as required for the project.</li><li>Check materials and finishes delivered to site against approved samples/specifications; keep registers updated.</li><li>Conduct site walks to verify workmanship, tolerances, and installation details; issue and close punch lists.</li><li>Lead coordination meetings with consultants and subcontractors; prepare agendas, minutes, and action trackers.</li><li>Monitor schedule impact of design changes; flag risks early and help plan recovery actions.</li><li>Keep project records well organized to meet company/ISO standards; support internal and external audits.</li><li>Promote safe work practices for architectural activities in coordination with WSH personnel.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Architecture, Architectural Technology, Building, or related field; equivalent experience considered.</li><li>Experience in architectural coordination for building projects is preferred.</li><li>Able to read and produce drawings/details; skilled in AutoCAD/Revit/BIM, and familiar with Navisworks or similar tools.</li><li>Understanding of local codes, standards, and typical client/consultant requirements.</li><li>Able to travel between project sites as needed.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79901 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
